      "ph": "Working title"
    },
    {
      "id": "b2",
      "type": "text",
      "html": "",
      "ph": "Open with the central idea, plainly. One or two sentences is enough — say what this is about and why it is worth a few minutes."
    },
    {
      "id": "b3",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "",
      "ph": "First section"
    },
    {
      "id": "b4",
      "type": "text",
      "html": "",
      "ph": "Make the point, then back it with a concrete example or a bit of evidence. Keep one idea per section."
    },
    {
      "id": "b5",
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "",
      "ph": "Second section"
    },
    {
      "id": "b6",
      "type": "text",
      "html": "",
      "ph": "Build on the first, or push against it. The turn is usually where a piece earns its length."
    },
    {
      "id": "b7",
      "type": "quote",
      "html": "",
      "cite": "",
      "ph": "Lift one line that carries the argument — a sentence a reader could quote back to you."
    },
    {
      "id": "b8",
      "type": "text",
      "html": "",
      "ph": "Close with what follows from all this: a practical implication, an open question, or a position you are willing to defend."
    },
